One of the most rapid rises to fame in the art world in recent years has been that of L. S. Lowry (1887- 1 976). Lowry painted for decades before achieving the recognition he deserved, and it was only in the last three or four years of his life that his true quality and originality were acknowledged. He has now become one of the best  loved of modern English painters.
